What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Body Dryer Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Global Body Dryer Market

The body dryer market is expected to be growing at a growth rate of 5.60% in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029 and is estimated to reach USD 6.30 billion by 2029.

A body dryer is an air dryer that replaces the use of a bath towel. Body dryers are used to dry the body properly after a shower by blowing warm air onto it. The air that is blown out is absorbed by a pod located on the underside of the top of the dryer. A fan, a heating element, and a motor are all included in the pod. In the bathroom, a body dryer can quickly create a spa-like ambiance.

The rising awareness about personal hygiene among consumers is likely to drive the demand for body dryer market. The rising level of disposable income of people and swift urbanization are some of the factors driving the wet-dry household vacuum cleaners market. Other significant factors such as the rise in the awareness among people about e-commerce platforms and the increasing number of populations across the globe will accelerate the market growth rate. Furthermore, improved lifestyle of consumers encouraging them to prefer luxury as well as quality products such as body dryers will positively impact the market's growth rate. Additionally, rise in the risk of spreading infectious disease among patients in hospitals, the increasing number of geriatric patients and patients with disability or inadequate mobility are the various factors forcing the healthcare sector to set up body dryers in hospitals to reduce risk of disease transmission. Hence, this will further cushion the growth rate of market.

Moreover, the rising preference of consumers towards smart homes and smart bathrooms will create lucrative market growth opportunities in the forecast period of 2022-2029. Also, the rising popularity of body dryers and technological advancement will escalate the market's growth rate in the future.

However, the high cost of body dryer and the high cost associated with product maintenance and installation will hamper the market growth rate. Additionally, the negative impact of COVID-19 on supply chain will hinder market growth. Availability of alternative products such as towels and wipes will further challenge the market in the forecast period mentioned above.

